data.title: Office Properties Income Trust, based in Newton, Mass., is reducing debt and strengthening balance sheet by entering into a restructuring support agreement with note holders of senior secured notes due September 2029, aiming to substantially deleverage.
data.description: In Newton, Massachusetts, Office Properties Income Trust (OPI) revealed a Restructuring Support Agreement with the September 2029 Ad Hoc Group of senior secured note holders. This agreement aims to restructure the corporate debt of OPI and enable significant deleveraging of its balance sheet. The agreement involves senior secured notes due September 2029. This move is crucial for OPI to improve its financial standing and reduce debt, underscoring a strategic effort to enhance the company's financial health.

data.title: HK regulator ramps up oversight on digital assets to protect investors from risks related to cryptocurrency holdings. #HongKong #regulation #cryptocurrency
data.description: The Securities and Futures Commission (SFC) in Hong Kong has increased monitoring of digital asset treasuries to safeguard investors from potential risks linked to cryptocurrency holdings. This move comes as part of efforts to ensure investor protection and is in response to the growing prominence of digital assets in the financial sector. By focusing on these assets, the SFC aims to enhance oversight and mitigate any associated risks for investors. This heightened scrutiny by the SFC underscores the importance of regulating the digital asset market effectively to safeguard investor interests in a rapidly evolving financial landscape.

data.title: Kia announces pricing for 2026 Niro HEV, continuing commitment to sustainable mobility.
data.description: Kia America recently revealed the pricing for the upcoming 2026 Niro HEV in Irvine, California. The company is dedicated to offering sustainable mobility solutions and cutting-edge design. The vehicle is tailored for individuals seeking a balance of versatility and efficiency while not compromising on comfort or technology. This release shows Kia's focus on innovation and meeting the demands of environmentally-conscious consumers.

data.title: Metallus extends labor contract by 90 days after USW members reject tentative agreement in Canton, Ohio.
data.description: In Canton, Ohio on October 30, 2025, Metallus (NYSE: MTUS), renowned for producing top-tier specialty metals, components, and supply chain services, announced that United Steelworkers (USW) Local 1123 members have rejected the proposed labor agreement through a voting process.

data.title: First National Bank Alaska declares $4.00 per share cash dividend for Q4 2025, payable on Dec. 15 to shareholders of record on Dec. 1.
data.description: In a recent Board of Directors meeting in Anchorage, Alaska on October 30, 2025, First National Bank Alaska (OTCQX:FBAK) announced a cash dividend of $4.00 per share for shareholders. The dividend will be payable on December 15, 2025, to shareholders of record as of December 1, 2025.
